cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image registration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning models for estimating the spatially-varying regularizer suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The regularization of velocity fields is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of variational methods and the estimation of spatio-temporal velocity fields suggest that the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the use of magnetic resonance images (MRI) and computed tomography (CT) images suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
